Posts.Content: Aug 9, 2007 01:15AM SandyInNJ63 wrote: Thanks Ann, both my oncologist and my primary doctor felt it could wait, but both said that if I was uncomfortable waiting that they had no problem sending me to a surgeon if that would give me peace of mind. Being neither of them seemed concerned about it, I decided it must be ok to wait. It's already been 3 months, so I really only have to wait 3 more months. In the meantime, I did alot of research on complex cysts and it seems there's a very very slight chance that the solid areas of the cyst would be malignant. I'm not too worried, but I also haven't forgotten about it either. "Probably" isn't good enough for someone that has had cancer already. Thanks for the good thoughts.

Posts.Content: Oct 5, 2007 03:28PM - edited Oct 5, 2007 03:30PM by SandyInNJ63 I was diagnosed with extensive Pagets, as well as invasive ductal carcinoma and DCIS (negative sentinal node).  5 years later I'm still doing great, no sign of cancer.  Hang in there, it's alot to deal but you will get through it.  This is a great resource for all your questions and concerns as well as amazing support.  Best wishes to you.
